title: JUIâ€™s Candidate Adnan Khan wins PK-101 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamiat Ulma-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI) Candidate Adnan Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-101, Bannu-III by securing 25,513 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Shah Muhammad Khan who bagged 21,369 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 36.02 per cent.
